BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 8 TASS -- Persuant to the Treaty of 
Civic Accord Russian President Boris Yeltsin has approved a 
schedule for preparing draft laws to be submitted to the State 
Duma in June, 1994. 
  The Russian president's representative in the Federal 
Assembly has been instructed to coordinate with the State Duma 
and the Russian Government to finalise draft laws to be 
considered by the lower house of parliament. 
  Among them are draft laws establishing the procedure for 
passing and enacting federal laws, amending the law on the state 
border, bills on the juridicial system in the Russian 
Federation, on the Russian Government, on fighting organised 
crime and others. 

